The paper proposes a technique for automatic repair of integer overflows in C source code, which involves static symbolic execution, detection, repair generation, and validation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves programming languages (cs.PL) as it deals with C source code. The paper also addresses security and cryptography (cs.CR) as integer overflows can pose a security threat. The paper's use of symbolic execution and validation suggests that it may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper's user study involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it compares the efficiency of IntRepair repairs to manual repairs.
